[{'created': '2013-12-26 19:23:20.000000000', 'message': 'Bugfix missing foreign key removal for mysql

Downgrading the cinder schema fails when running 018_add_qos_specs.py under MySQL. The
upgrade path of this schema patch adds the foreign key volume_types_ibfk_1 on table
volume_types, and the downgrade does not correspondingly remove it before attempting
to drop the qos_specs_id column.  This update removes the foreign key when the engine
is mysql prior to dropping the column.

commit_message:
Bugfix missing foreign key removal for mysql

Downgrading the cinder schema fails when running 018_add_qos_specs.py
under MySQL. The upgrade path of this schema patch adds the foreign
key volume_types_ibfk_1 on table volume_types, and the downgrade does
not correspondingly remove it before attempting to drop the
qos_specs_id column.  This update removes the foreign key when
the engine is mysql prior to dropping the column.

Change-Id: Ibd3b35ad3b0bd41ad04ab7aeeb28c3ba7e5d255d
Closes-Bug: #1264360

commit_message:
Relocated step to restart Neutron plug-in agent

Relocated step to restart Neutron plug-in agent from section for
plug-in configuration to after completion of Neutron configuration.
This change allows the plug-in agent to read all configured values
from neutron.conf required for proper start and operation.

commit_message:
Support dnsmasq_config_file option for dhcp-agent

Allow to configure dnsmasq_config_file for the dhcp-agent.
For common things like adapting the MTU size for instances
via DHCP.

closes-bug #1259495

Change-Id: Iee09eb9a66e84d49c0452fccf9c7d6bcb7ba8311

commit_message:
Updated endpoints to support paths and ssl

- Add {public,admin,internal}_url parameters to override other
  {public,admin,internal}_ parameters.
- Also change some 'real_' prefix into '_real' suffix to respect the
coding guide.
- Fixed parsing the ssl/enable value in the provider.
- Update examples

Change-Id: I78d2695eb5cb1287538afe154668da9fe23e62a3

I really need this change and it looks like Dan Bode doesn't have time for this change. I'll take ownership on it."}, {'account_id': 7822, 'date': '2013-12-24 00:33:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: (3 inline comments)

Just a few comments, and we can discuss how to move forward. I'd like to see the patch land because it's important for your use, so we can move forward with getting it in. However, I think that we can tighten it up a bit. To start, I think the methods should be documented, mainly just to clarify what's going into the methods and what's expected to come out.

On a larger scale, we might want to think about moving away from having the caches attached to the cache in such a raw way. Rather, I think it would be cleaner to write a testable cache class (say UserTenantCache) that could then be attached to the keystone_user_role provider class. It's a subtle distinction, but one that separates the logic of pulling the information into memory in an efficient way and the logic of creating/updating/deleting the keystone_user_role.

Let me know how you want to move forward, and how I can help draft up any of the code."}, {'account_id': 7822, 'date': '2013-12-24 00:34:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

To clarify on the last statement, when I said 'cache on the cache' I meant 'cache on the class'."}, {'account_id': 7156, 'date': '2013-12-25 09:35:22.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

I agree with the overall direction you suggest as I don't fully agree with the need to prefetch everything just to support purge.

However, my wish is for this patch to land ASAP so I don't have to maintain it myself anymore. I have tested this patch in production and have been using it for months without any issue. Whenever I remove it, it's the apocalypse: Puppet takes 8 minutes to run instead of 30 seconds.

If we have to do a rewrite, I suggest we do it in a separated change. 2 very similar changes have already landed for keystone_user and keystone_tenant custom types, this was the only remaining one to get merged."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-12-26 18:55:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: No score

commit_message:
Refactor keystone_user_role to be lazier

Currently, the entire list of user roles are
cached ASAP. Trying to pre-determine these
is very slow b/c there is no user role list
command in keystone, so you must iterate through
all tenant/user combinations to retrieve the list.

This patch makes the retrieval of all state info
lazy.

Partial-Bug: 1224179
Change-Id: I80a85f3ddf2c41fe447df5682ad31ac4df8f8b59

I've not analyzed the patch TBH, just a comment on the approach. Validating an image after partial download could be complex and not cover all cases. Perhaps it could be simplified to verifying a checksum or something?
Also the approach taken in libvirt for example is to auto nuke an image if there is any issue with transfer using code like:

    with fileutils.remove_path_on_error(path):

commit_message:
VMWare - Fix a image upload is interrupted it's not cleaned up

If an image is upload is interrupted, the file check will succeed
though the image is invalid.  Subsequent boots will then fail.
This validates the file and re-uploads if an invalid file is found

Change-Id: I884bdc16bc8ad0fdcdb20e53ee54e62f29f331ef
Fixes: bug #1213269

commit_message:
Add new haproxy section

Since https://github.com/openstack/neutron/commit/bf8949defc24af3636da417442469e7d7194c7b3
got merged, we have now a new section in
LBaaS configuration file: [haproxy].

This patch aims to add this section and also to fix user_group flag to
be part of this new section.

Change-Id: I6c13e550a7033daa8ae6164b0437dfbc16a07666
Closes-bug: #1263952
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Ensure ML2 plugin package is installed

Some platforms have a package for ML2 plugin.

This change makes sure is it installed for those platforms when
ML2 plugin is used and configured.

Change-Id: I24c8eb7d17a462b63d2023027c90da7f876f7503
Closes-bug: #1264205

commit_message:
Fix workspace setup

Stable branch overrides for client testing, devstack-gate alternate-branch
testing, and grenade old/new branch selection are all actually the same
thing.  Update setup_project to reflect that, fixing all known bugs in
the process.  Note that some jobs will need to be updated to pass in
OVERRIDE_ZUUL_BRANCH.

This is an update to the previously reverted change to add testing and a fix
for an issue seen in production.  The resulting code is actually simpler, but
it is worth noting that the check to ensure that at some point the ZUUL_REF
for the project was checked out has been removed.

Change-Id: Ie0c4b30878896684cc2faf02dee1ea222594ae6d

commit_message:
Add qos_specs support to solidfire driver

We've added a new qos_specs object to Cinder that allows creation
and management of qos settings separate from volume-types.
Now instead of embedding the qos info in the extra-specs of the
volume-type we associate the desired qos-spec to a volume-type.

This change implements the capability of the SolidFire driver to
take advantage of that feature.

Change-Id: I215bd0cff0c0a91c106de27eea9ec2b91689a46e
Implements: blueprint add-qosspecs-support-to-solidfire-driver

commit_message:
Handle initialize_connection() exception in volume manager

Due to the fact that several drivers require backend communication to fetch
connection information for a volume, it's possile that these driver throw
exceptions while doing that.  Currently exceptions can bubble up to volume
API not being handled.  This patch logs exception in volume manager and
then raises VolumeBackendAPIException to caller.

Change-Id: Ib3cc152e04ba029dd835a64b0cfb0a77b8a6828e
Closes-bug: 1256804

commit_message:
VMware: validate data returned by task prior to access

Ensure that the data returned by the polling task for
SearchDatastore_Task is valid.

In addition to this the patch reduces the waiting time from
2 seconds to 1 second.

Change-Id: If0b66eb6c826f89b469ca5a5aad36299b7a70213
Closes-bug: #1254128

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-10-17 18:09:59.000000000', 'message': 'NFS: fail when image is bigger than the volume

When creating a new volume from a qcow2 image stored in glance, we will
be given the pysical size of the image instead of the virtual size.
Drivers like glusterfs and nfs will convert that image to raw after
downloading and resize it to the requested size afterwards.

If the virtual size of the image is bigger than the requested one, the
resulting volume might end up being unusable after the resize even
though the creation went good.

This patch will make the volume creation to fail if the virtual size of
the image exceeds the one in the requested volume.

Fixes bug 1235358

Change-Id: I254cd9e3acf5d9eb7eb913b37d27a14e97568dec

commit_message:
Fail when image is bigger than the volume

When creating a new volume from a qcow2 image stored in glance, we will
be given the physical size of the image instead of the virtual size.
Most drivers will convert that image to raw after downloading for
resizing it to the requested volume size afterwards.

If the virtual size of the image is bigger than the requested one, the
resulting volume might end up being unusable after the resize even
though the creation went good.

This patch will make the volume creation fail if the virtual size of
the image exceeds the one of the requested volume.

Closes-Bug: #1235358
Change-Id: I254cd9e3acf5d9eb7eb913b37d27a14e97568dec

commit_message:
Marks running backup FAILED with Instance deletion

Reasons:
- When an instance is deleted,
  its active backup is left in BUILD/NEW state.
- This backup for a deleted instance cannot be deleted.

Changes:
- Checks if backup is running before deleting the instance.
- Fails the running backup prior to deleting the requested instance.

Change-Id: I1670aad4cda6bb991c5d8fd76b8b7c233009c638
Closes-Bug: #1220989

commit_message:
Graph action refactoring

* get rid of dependency counter in graph action:
  analyze graph directly instead when we need to determine nodes we
  need to execute or revert next;
* move graph interpreting to separate class, GraphAnalyzer:
  instead of inheriting this code from base graph action we now use
  composition;
* get rid of direct dependency of graph action on engine.

Relates to blueprint smart-revert
Co-authored-by: Ivan A. Melnikov <imelnikov@griddynamics.com>
Change-Id: Ib6499d2f2d5b568d7f2a45af3c5ed6d8d9ace39b

A single DBAPI instance is created globally in Nova at module import time.
If we initialize the DB backend as soon as a DBAPI instance is created,
we simplify code a lot, get rid of the lock and remove the overhead of
checking if the backend has been initialized from every __getattr__() call.

See original patch in oslo - I9fdf3eab32ee0f078d64fbde35df81c2d1123ae2

'}]
commit_message:
[POC] Remove lazy loading of database backend

A single DBAPI instance is created globally in Nova at module import time.
If we initialize the DB backend as soon as a DBAPI instance is created,
we simplify code a lot, get rid of the lock and remove the overhead of
checking if the backend has been initialized from every __getattr__() call.

See original patch in oslo - I9fdf3eab32ee0f078d64fbde35df81c2d1123ae2

Change-Id: Icfce52507338c093d485c0e5dc1760331d818b13

Fix for deletion of nano flavor in OSTF

Add smoke_flavor attribute to setUpClass of SmokeChecksTest
to prevent AttributeError upon tearDownClass invocation
from smoke tests that don`t use it.
Modify HeatBaseTest and TestStackActions classes so that
they support changes.

Change-Id: I33beb5e014781fb12ad45a212f4f81b9d7d324ca
Closes-bug: #1263667

commit_message:
Move ScenarioRunner class to a separate module

For the sake of good structural code organization, we move here the central
benchmark engine class, namely the ScenarioRunner, to a separate module. We
also change the test code correspondingly and slightly rename some of the
methods left in the 'utils' module.

Blueprint benchmark-engine-refactoring

Change-Id: Id2cdad7f34c2ce067ad155c13166e256072a47e6

commit_message:
Wait for HDFS readiness after datanode services start

Bug #1240511 consists of two connected problems:
1. oozie-setup.sh exists with status code 0 when error occurs.
2. Savanna expects that HDFS is running immediately
   after "/usr/sbin/hadoop-daemon.sh start datanode" execution

This patch addresses the second issue.
The first issue is addressed by https://review.openstack.org/#/c/62511/

Added check that all datanodes are running before manipulations with HDFS.

Fixes bug #1240511

Change-Id: I953512e2b430fba562ee3dceb8c1781aa8ad61bf

commit_message:
Add possibility to build iso with specific nailgun/astute/ostf gerrit commits

Some modifications in order to provide support for ISO build with specific nailgun/astute/ostf gerrit commits.
Gerrit URLs and commits can be passed via environment variables.

Change-Id: I32b78c2b850b0f7c9c5d9028cad160eeb9a3b75c

Now for KVM when resume an instance with block storage, nova
compute will throw exception and failed to resume the VM.

The root cause is that when resume a VM with block storage,
libvirt driver needs to call conductor via rpcapi to update
block device, but the function of resume() do not have context,
this will cause RPC api failed.

Change-Id: I712777ed1d893a2b6463d30c407b0a677e37b602
Closes-Bug: #1241337
(cherry picked from commit de4158861000dedc204314c545cc5682aa38f5f1)
'}]
commit_message:
Add context as parameter for resume

Now for KVM when resume an instance with block storage, nova
compute will throw exception and failed to resume the VM.

The root cause is that when resume a VM with block storage,
libvirt driver needs to call conductor via rpcapi to update
block device, but the function of resume() do not have context,
this will cause RPC api failed.

Change-Id: I712777ed1d893a2b6463d30c407b0a677e37b602
Closes-Bug: #1241337
(cherry picked from commit de4158861000dedc204314c545cc5682aa38f5f1)

commit_message:
port servers negative tests into v3 Part2

this ports servers negative tests into v3and do some
corresponding change in the client. this also ports
shelve and create_backup tests into v3, add v3 support
in wait_for_server_status. this also removes the negative
test for personality, because it has been removed in nova
v3 api.

this also does some sync from v2 tests, applies the following
commit in v3 tests:
I4b06b148b5d9bceda0cef2d2bb5f3b72325928ac
I5b423b3424e1dfe6cf5f8fef0dc9538961c1f28d
Ibd04a1fdaab74fe59bcf16cc99d4ecf4821f4ae2

Partially implements blueprint nova-v3-api-tests

Change-Id: Ibfe22c33c26e39b86975965bbac0cc76a5f8836e

commit_message:
VMware: deal with concurrent downloads

Two issues have been dealt with:
1. moving the temporarary image directory - check that it exists
   prior to the move
2. creation of the root vmdk file - create a temporary one and then
   move to the destination

Closes-bug: #1230047

Change-Id: I7a5cba9cadb4b04527985c987db17f5ac2f1b994

commit_message:
Passing configuration name to a driver

For the ability to load same driver as a service provider
with different configurations, a service provider name is passed
to a driver when instantiated.
So driver configuration name in configuration file is not hardcoded
in code anymore.

Change-Id: I2eb4c52838f76245e77f280b7251b2338f4464f3
Closes-Bug: #1264111

commit_message:
Replace xrange in for loop with range

xrange is not supported in python 3, so replace it with range.
It's not a large range size, so no need to use six.moves.range.

Change-Id: Ie62c3f1651d98f6b7d9a70fa1b485a9a04fd758f
Closes-Bug: #1264182

explanation='message'.
Ex.

commit_message:
Fixed the invalid argument at subclass of webob.exc.WSGIHTTPException

If the specific error message is required, we must set
explanation='message'.
Ex.
OK: raise webob.exc.HTTPBadRequest(explanation='What?')
NG: raise webob.exc.HTTPBadRequest('What?')

Change-Id: I8d1adeb95cef455bfeb5a805c7f7db7bf05e236e
Closes-Bug: #1264223

commit_message:
Use model_query() in db.*****_destroy

Use model_query() instead of session.query in db.volume_destroy,
db.volume_type_destroy, db.transfer_destroy and db.snapshot_destroy as
other methods use.
model_query function is the query helper which is used in most part of
cinder/db/sqlalchemy/api.py.

Change-Id: I97be252df9d40bb97231e3341d5cedec26af2d93
Closes-Bug: #1256483
(cherry picked from commit d54c49a22e3ce147003cc9a926b7b72e8dc9c1a8)

commit_message:
Automatic login after password changed

Currently when a user changed the password successfully,
it will redirect to the login page, the user needs to
input the username and new password to relogin. This will
allow user to automatic login after password changed from
settings and users panal.

Implements blueprint auto-login-after-password-changed

Change-Id: I550f7738067a340cd2e2a89385099dcff22f56e0

commit_message:
Remove remaining code from compute __init__

This commit just removes the remaining code from __init__.py in the
compute api directory. We don't want tempest to require a working
config or any other external requirements at import time.

Change-Id: Iec03167dc6e0502c83a1f4db216abd899d89545c

commit_message:
Enable tests of Swift which does not use auth system

This patch enables functional tests for Swift which is not combined with
any auth system such as Keystone or TempAuth. Insert test skip annotations
to test codes which are invalid when auth system is not used.

Change-Id: Ia99dfb8f30de14b9f6b4f3ad9dd2ddb11d8d0755
Implements: blueprint swift-test-without-keystone

commit_message:
Novaclient should use cliutils from oslo

Currently, it defines its own set of decorators to define
command line arguments. This code is exactly the same as that
in oslo.cliutils. Thus it would be easier to maintain the code
at one place.

Some more functions are duplicated. But those currently do not
work on py33 and needs to be fixed in oslo.cliutils

Change-Id: Ia85ecb00903713644e9584fde564a74d6d43f22e
Partial-Bug: #1261850

commit_message:
Have tox install via setup.py develop

tox 1.6 was released, which means that we can now take advantage of
the feature we added to it - which is using setup.py develop to
install the code into the virtualenv. The logic was taken from
run_tests.sh - so the performance issues around using tox vs. using
install_venv should now be gone.

Additionally, override the tox pip install command to avoid using the
"--pre" option which is the default in tox.  "--pre" means "Include
pre-release and development versions."  By default, pip will only
install stable versions of software, and that is the behavior we want.

Change-Id: Ida5e440d1bdb9f8e9031277ea53a02d2ef171438
Co-Authored-By: Monty Taylor <mordred@inaugust.com>

delete the stack that was created (and already deleted) in

Closes-Bug: #1262286

commit_message:
Fix: Heat test deletes the same stack twice

When BaseOrchestrationTest.tearDownClass is called, it tries to
delete the stack that was created (and already deleted) in
test_stack_crud_no_resources.  This patch removes the stack from the
stacks list to prevent that from happening.

Change-Id: Iaad6d3bb0b9c1f9289a7907fe8c082baeceeba27
Closes-Bug: #1262286

formatting should not use locals().

commit_message:
Catch NotImplementedError for spice in the api

When a driver doesn't provide spice consoles, it will raise
NotImplementedError back up to the API.  Catch this and return a 501.

Change-Id: Ib417ad7627d07d6b26abfa171f346e4e63f612ca

commit_message:
Clean up the test cases to use the real UUID

Object models have a UUID field type and expect to check is_uuid_like.
If the strings like 'fake-uuid' are used, the check will fail.
The patch is to replace the 'fake-uuid' like strings with the real UUIDs.

Change-Id: I96a68dc3b2531f87fa8c8498e9d4f6b50ed905a0

commit_message:
Add error check to baselineCPU call in libvirt driver

In some cases getbaselineCPU returns -1. This changes adds a check for
that in addition to None to avoid a subsequent failure when attempting
to parse the return value as a string.

Change-Id: I925efaf100b380c548b1216a6affe6bd1b37a437
Closes-Bug: #1261938

commit_message:
Refactors network scenario test to support more network tests

1. Moves some functions of TestNetworkBasicOps class to
scenario/manager.py.
2. Changes variables management style in TestNetworkBasicOps
class. Moves variables(keypairs, security_groups, networks etc.)
defination from setUpClass function to test function.

Change-Id: I51e7884fd24ae3d09889203691d43ab23f4d9ecf

commit_message:
make cms token id URL safe

Previous cms token id's were not URL safe nor did they use RFC
compliant encodings. Use urlsafe base64 encoding as described in
RFC-4648 to generate the cms token id. Also strip the trailing pad
character(s) as suggested in RFC-4648 to be fully URL safe. Use
Python's base64.urlsafe_b64encode() and base64.urlsafe_b64decode() to
perform the encode/decode operations. See bug report for complete
issue description. The implementation utilizes functions in
keystone.common.base64utils and keystone.common.pem_utils which appear
in prior commit for this bug.

Change-Id: I85c53669e86e301d3a89ca413a5520b582d754d3
Fixes-Bug: #1233838

commit_message:
Disallow negative image sizes

Currently Glance v1 allows creation of images with negative sizes when
the source URL provided by the --location parmeter does not exist at
the time of creation.

There is already a check to verify whether or not an image size can be
converted to an int but the check doesn't verify whether or not the
resulting value is >= 0. This commit supplements that check to
disallow negative values for the size parameter.

Change-Id: I2ae648c4a3e17f6ffb03a635eef9098d79ea8a2b
Closes-Bug: #1260738

commit_message:
POC: rolling upgrade test for nova-compute

This is a hard coded proof of concept of a rolling upgrade test for
nova-compute.  Nova wants to support the ability to run stable/havana
nova-compute with icehouse everything else. This sets up a test for
that.

Full support for this will come in a separate series of patches. This is
to just show the idea.

Change-Id: I157ff04d3c03fc925e44e05a7fa45011c481aa83

Stable branch overrides for client testing, devstack-gate alternate-branch
testing, and grenade old/new branch selection are all actually the same
thing.  Update setup_project to reflect that, fixing all known bugs in
the process.  Note that some jobs will need to be updated to pass in
OVERRIDE_ZUUL_BRANCH.

Change-Id: I6613715439bed9914b8444e335fac5eab4d14075
'}]
commit_message:
Fix workspace setup

Stable branch overrides for client testing, devstack-gate alternate-branch
testing, and grenade old/new branch selection are all actually the same
thing.  Update setup_project to reflect that, fixing all known bugs in
the process.  Note that some jobs will need to be updated to pass in
OVERRIDE_ZUUL_BRANCH.

Change-Id: I6613715439bed9914b8444e335fac5eab4d14075

I'm curious about why it doesn't. Also, could we perform this check in the api layer instead of the db layer? I wonder if this bug is present in glance v2 as well."}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2013-10-20 06:06:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I think maybe there are something wrong with the glance client, since bug https://bugs.launchpad.net/python-glanceclient/+bug/1240462 is also talking similar issue. So it would be nice to clarify why the code in line 790-791 can't catch this issue, as ameade mentioned above. Thanks."}, {'account_id': 6737, 'date': '2013-10-20 15:59:46.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 6737, 'date': '2013-10-20 16:04:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Alex, the case I am tying to cover here is where a request has gone beyond that check and then another request comes in. If we check the status during the locked sqlalchemy session then we know we can rely on it. I pointed out that we would ultimately need to have a proper taskflow here but this is just an interim safeguard. Take a look at the unit test to see that case i am trying to cover.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-10-20 16:43:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Doesn't seem to work

"}, {'account_id': 177, 'date': '2013-10-20 21:42:32.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I think I understand the case your test is trying to cover. When an image is in saving status, another request to update the image with image data should fail with an HTTP 409.

If I revert all of these changes except for the new test, it still passes. However, if I remove this line: https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/api/v1/images.py#L791 it then fails.

I'm not sure if there is another issue here or not. I think what Fei was alluding to is that if someone issues two image-update requests with glance client, both with data, then they will both succeed. This is because glanceclient will grab the image before it issues the request and only actually send the data if the image is in queued state.

What was it that caused you to notice the issue? Could you elaborate? Sorry, not trying to drag this out. If anything we need this test to cover this case.

P.S. We are moving away from using mox (not py3 compat) and using mock instead

Thanks!"}, {'account_id': 6549, 'date': '2013-10-21 04:46:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

According to the checking at [1] (and [2] if you using glanceclient trigger image-update request), I consider this issue is happen on race condition context only. So dosaboy's change is make sense to me to add a checking for image status during the locked sqlalchemy session (adding to api controller is useless since we have no distributed lock mechanism).

In future we can add a upload taskflow which contains necessary reversion for the status transfer task to make sure image's status can be restored to 'queue' from 'saving' if glance-api service dies during the uploading flow execution.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/api/v1/images.py#L791
[2] https://github.com/openstack/python-glanceclient/blob/master/glanceclient/v1/shell.py#L298

Thanks for the commit dosaboy. Could you please do unit test better as Alex Meade mentioned.

BTW, I'm also thinking, under current glance design, can we add a checking when glance-api daemon restart, and do the necessary image status status reversion such as change 'saving' back to 'queue'?"}, {'account_id': 6737, 'date': '2013-10-21 20:43:40.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-10-21 21:17:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Doesn't seem to work

removing my -1 until I can make more sense!'}, {'account_id': 6493, 'date': '2013-11-21 20:24:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I really do not like doing state transition enforcement in the DB layer.  I understand that this is an interim solution, however these things have a way of living on.

It seems that this points at a greater issue in glance.  We do not have a good way to manage states.  In this case it appears that we are trying to disallow the image state transition from saving -> saving.  Is it possible to find an interim solution that enforces this in a more appropriate place in the code?"}, {'account_id': 616, 'date': '2013-11-21 23:50:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(I think my sentiment at least partially agrees with John's. In any case I'm just trying to clarify my idea from earlier on this review.)

I think the right solution for this right now is to make the action to set the image status from 'SAVING' to 'ACTIVE' exclusive and atomic. In straight SQL this would look something like

'UPDATE images SET status = "active" WHERE id="blah" AND status = "saving"'

If no rows are affected, then you know something went wrong. When it goes wrong, we should remove added location, if any, and delete what was put up on the store. Basically, the loser in an update race recognizes that he has lost (relying on atomicity in the DB) and cleans up the mess.

Sound sensible? This will probably entail a minor change to the db api for image_update I guess.'}, {'account_id': 6493, 'date': '2013-11-22 08:47:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

markwash: While I like your solution a bit better, that still sounds like the DB would be doing the enforcement.  If this issue is critical enough in the short term to require such a kludge then perhaps that is what needs to be done, but it would probably be best if that was clear.

Further, I am hoping that no data will actually be uploaded before this failure occurs.  I think that is case, but perhaps we should verify that as well.'}, {'account_id': 6549, 'date': '2013-11-24 05:54:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8: No score

btw, actually I still think dosboy just try to do an interim solution to quick fix this defect for glance. Anyway, more thinking will be better always."}, {'account_id': 6737, 'date': '2013-11-26 14:40:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

Ok, so I've done a bit more testing on this.

Firstly to be clear, the issue this patch aims to resolve is where concurrent
requests for the same image hit the api and are processed such that more than
one request manages to transition the image from 'queued' to 'saving'. This is
obviously a very small window - the time between the api checking the status
and the regsitry processing the state change - and as such is hard to hit.
Using scenario tests that triggering multiple concurrent update requests to
upload data to an already 'queued' image, I was not able to reproduce the
error. Having said that, the unit test provided as part of this patchset
hopefully highlights the case where the error can theoretically occur.

Now, as it stands this patch can have the side effect of images getting stuck
if upload does not complete and the image remains in 'saving' state. A common
and easily reproducible example of this is if the glance api restarts mid
update/upload. Thing is, this behaviour currently exists anyway if the api gets
restarted wile the image is in 'saving' state, so applying this new patch would
close another gap while not actually creating any new side effects.

If we still don't want to go down this route then I can't see any other way to
achieve this protection without a much larger code change which, as previously
pointed out, would likely involve modifications to the db api since the only
unit of atomitcity across nodes that we currently have in Glance (afaik) is the
db session. I may well be wrong though and welcome comments/suggestions. (I am,
by the way, ignoring any potential taskflow work since this was only ever
intended as an interim solution.)"}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-12-04 06:03:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

be to implement a new taskflow for (at least) uploads thus avoiding
issues if the Glance service dies. This interim solution is simply
to guard against requests occuring during the processing of a valid
upload request by refusing to service any further requests while
the image is still 'saving'.

commit_message:
Adds guard against upload contention

Protect against concurrent image uploads by allowing the
initial request to proceed and succeed and subsequent
concurrent requests to fail.

We now allow the upload activation to specify what state
it expects to transition to 'active' from. If by the time
the db is updated the transition has already occured i.e.
another upload has succeeded, the upload will fail and data
will be cleaned up.

Fixes: bug 1241025
Change-Id: Ie532b61484bec660910fb9a37429397bde8ef11f

commit_message:
Add option for enabling debug logs only for OpenStack

A new option --debug-openstack-only was introduced to enable debug logs
for OpenStack components, but not for external ones (e.g. ampq). Synced
from oslo-incubator.

Change-Id: I635af310896a11cab0d16756ec3d03b942454dcf
Closes-Bug: #1207576

commit_message:
Refactoring driver interfaces

Added method create_share_form_snapshot to
manila.share.driver.ShareDriver.

Removed methods allocate_container, allocate_container_from_snapshot,
create_export, deallocate_container, remove_export

Implements bp refacto-driver-interfaces

Change-Id: I9f1c26b189f50aedc8e19864a172557700adf849

To avoid *silent* truncation of columns in mysql
it is much safer to turn on traditional mode which
behaves in the normal manner.

From the mysql docs:

Make MySQL behave like a "traditional" SQL database system.
A simple description of this mode is "give an error instead
of a warning" when inserting an incorrect value into a column.

Change-Id: Ic62af8514c377d2b8c934449116498855e03d7bd
'}]
commit_message:
Ensure that mysql traditional mode is enabled

To avoid *silent* truncation of columns in mysql
it is much safer to turn on traditional mode which
behaves in the normal manner.

From the mysql docs:

Make MySQL behave like a "traditional" SQL database system.
A simple description of this mode is "give an error instead
of a warning" when inserting an incorrect value into a column.

Change-Id: Ic62af8514c377d2b8c934449116498855e03d7bd

commit_message:
Move async utils to own file

Instead of mixing eventlet related utility
functionality with async utility functionality
it seems to make sense to seperate those types
into two different files.

commit_message:
Add --object-name

Add parameter --object-name, which:
1) Sets target object name when upload single file
2) Sets object prefix when upload a directory

Change-Id: Idc4357c3355e66d31c100540b901e70db20b03c3
Closes-Bug: 1012979

(2 inline comments)

On the topic of generalizing this for full filter validation and for supporting other use cases.

It is true all active filters are currently evaluated, though not all filter_properties are set, leading to some of them just passing OK on every host. Also you have limited filtering to only happen if hints are set.

For missing filter_properties, a quick scan of the current set of filters gave me at least three missing properties: extra_specs, group_hosts and pci_requests. The last two are currently only added for initial scheduling by the scheduler itself in filter_scheduler.py, based on hints provided with the request.

For other use cases, I can see this being used for both evacuate and cold migrations (admin initiated) when those operations target a specific host. Not sure cold migrations support that just yet, but eventually it might.

My point being that the method should be named after what it does (filter validation of a host) and not after whom might call it. I think validate_scheduler_hints_for_live_migration is artificially limiting this to live migrations and also misses out on that it does general filtering as well as hints validation."}, {'account_id': 7450, 'date': '2013-09-20 13:17:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: (2 inline comments)

'}, {'account_id': 7450, 'date': '2013-09-20 14:18:31.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 7450, 'date': '2013-09-20 14:19:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

Thanks Hans for your remarks !

I've done the following modifications:
    - removed the restriction if hints are set or not
    - added _get_filter_properties() method which create filter_properties 
    - added "group_hosts" and "pci_request" to filter_properties but extra_specs is part of instance_type and it's already in filter_properties
    - renamed "validate_scheduler_hints_for_live_migration" into "validate_host_by_scheduler"

Could you please validate these modifictions, thanks !'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-09-20 14:34:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 6: Doesn't seem to work

I think you'll need to bump the migration version to at least 227 to avoid the block reserved for Havana backport fixes

You are changing a V2 API by adding an additional parameter, and other proposals to do this have always been bounced in favor of having to add a new extension so that clients can tell what is and isn't supported.

commit_message:
Validate target host by scheduler

In the current implementation, when we boot a server we can
provide additional placement information through the scheduler
hints mechanism. However, when we live migrate a server those
scheduler hints are not taken into account.

This patch adds the ability to check if the target host passes
filters before live migration. To achieve that task those
hints are persisted as a json blob into the database.

This additional verification can leave the system locked, for
instance two hosts which run servers that must be located on
different hosts can't be migrated. Thus, an option
'no-check-by-scheduler' has been set up in order to make this
verification optional.

DocImpact

blueprint validate-targethost-live-migration
Fixes: bug #1198977
Fixes: bug #1039065

Change-Id: I38e198283332bedc5473246c69feab1ef9693a72

commit_message:
Fix usage of get() methods in python clients

Here, we replace passing the reference to a resource to the get() method of
python client managers by passing the ID of the resource. While the previous
approach worked for Nova, it turned out to be a bug in Cinder.

We also fix the list/dict objects used as the parameter defaults, which is
a bad approach as well.

Change-Id: I9baa805b0aa3f7ccc704a2fa64a057858034977c
Closes-Bug: #1263770

commit_message:
Have tox install via setup.py develop

tox 1.6 was released, which means that we can now take advantage of the
feature we added to it - which is using setup.py develop to install the
code into the virtualenv. The logic was taken from run_tests.sh - so the
performance issues around using tox vs. using install_venv should now be
gone.

run_tests.sh is still needed to handle the ui switching between
parallel, single and debug modes to testr.

Original change to Nova: Ida5e440d1bdb9f8e9031277ea53a02d2ef171438

Change-Id: I946f2255ea6d47d1e99676e21da9e06620b1c779

commit_message:
Support for Windows in Virtualbox scripts

Added support for Cygwin.
Increased default disk and memory sizes for compatibility with Heat.
Added checks for non-installed Cygwin components.
Default NIC type changed to faster AMD PCnet FAST III.
Added check on network settings application.
Added trick to increase network configuration stability under Windows.
Changed hard-coded interface addition part to automatic loop.
Removed extra whitespaces.
Changed Fuel Web to Mirantis OpenStack
Rebased to latest commit.

Closes-Bug: #1252314
Change-Id: I466ebec87506eade5164de7d27d73f10dbbea0d9

commit_message:
allow hypervisors to be down but still pass

This test case is pretty raw, but it does make some invalid
assumptions about using the first hypervisor for everything. In
the uptime case it really needs to loop over all of them otherwise
if the first hypervisor is disabled this will fail.

This also does a cleanup refactoring of the hypervisor list check.

Change-Id: I9c3db794269f61aaaa55d432b14edf2d0fd1c774
Closes-Bug: #1193194

commit_message:
Added step to make sure 'root_helper' key references 'neutron'

In the current Neutron Havana packages for RHEL-style distributions,
the default 'root_helper' key in neutron.conf references 'quantum'
instead of 'neutron'. This issue should get fixed upstream, but in
the meantime I added a step to make sure this key references
'neutron'.

Change-Id: I25f9faaba1067040829633aff990d238f5bf4ced
backport: havana
Closes-Bug: #1258309
(cherry picked from commit 5dc7f610d57b79ac133b48725df1c669f525add8)

I fixed the AMQP configuration steps in cinder.conf for Block Storage
on both controller and service nodes. I also unified structure and
phrasing with other portions of the guide and mentioned replacing
'RABBIT_PASS'. This patch affects all distributions.

I also found and fixed a minor issue causing several database
configuration instructions for other distributions to leak into those
for Debian which uses Debconf.

Change-Id: Ifd6f185b422195a00aad6efa83418d34b93eac85
backport: havana
Closes-Bug: #1244781
(cherry picked from commit a5fd95d740fa0e6c992dfdd401e2e64d050e5600)
"}]
commit_message:
Fixed AMQP configuration steps for Block Storage

I fixed the AMQP configuration steps in cinder.conf for Block Storage
on both controller and service nodes. I also unified structure and
phrasing with other portions of the guide and mentioned replacing
'RABBIT_PASS'. This patch affects all distributions.

I also found and fixed a minor issue causing several database
configuration instructions for other distributions to leak into those
for Debian which uses Debconf.

Change-Id: Ifd6f185b422195a00aad6efa83418d34b93eac85
backport: havana
Closes-Bug: #1244781
(cherry picked from commit a5fd95d740fa0e6c992dfdd401e2e64d050e5600)

commit_message:
Moves negative tests from api/compute/servers/test_virtual_interfaces

This change set moves the negative tests in test_virtual_interfaces to
a new file test_virtual_interfaces_negative

Also changes line # 43, rand_name(#$%*&^%) to uuid4() to get the invalid
server ID in negative file and removes usage of modules directly.

Note: HACKING.rst
The second requirement is that all negative tests must be added to a negative
test file. If such a file doesn't exist for the particular resource being
tested a new test file should be added

So I'd like to wait for their comments.

@Chris:

We found one xml/json consistency of Nova v2 API with this patch, and it has been fixed in v3 API.
Should we fix it in v2 API also?

The detail is https://review.openstack.org/#/c/60406/11/tempest/api/compute/admin/test_hosts_negative.py ."}, {'account_id': 5292, 'date': '2013-12-10 00:49:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 11:

commit_message:
Enable HostsAdminTestXML

Although there is hosts_client class for XML, HostsAdminTestXML is
disabled. This patch enables HostsAdminTestXML.

Change-Id: Ib136661107a94f3e2c1607dad644dce0a3b42502
Closes-Bug: #1261968

Update oslo-incubator processutils module

instead of jsonutils.dumps(). An error will happen like the following:

commit_message:
Fix JSON serilization in objects

The test case will check whether JSON serializable by json.dumps()
instead of jsonutils.dumps(). An error will happen like the following:

TypeError: <nova.objects.flavor.Flavor object at 0x4e8a150> is not
JSON serializable.

The patch is to add support to json serialization.

Change-Id: I686f9c34b915c369439947d79ad1df627428a424

commit_message:
Update oslo-incubator log module

Changes -
 * Use hacking import_exceptions for gettextutils._

[{'created': '2013-12-17 03:55:16.000000000', 'message': 'Make sure report_interval is less than service_down_time

If service_down_time is less than report_interval, services will
routinely be considered down, because they report in too rarely.
Add check for service_down_time vs report_interval, if report_interval
is larger than service_down_time, automatically change
service_down_time to be report_interval * 2.5 .

Closes bug #1261611

Change-Id: Icfa2a79d9df45a9674e8312f6ce67bc5a38275d2
'}]
commit_message:
Make sure report_interval is less than service_down_time

If service_down_time is less than report_interval, services will
routinely be considered down, because they report in too rarely.
Add check for service_down_time vs report_interval, if report_interval
is larger than service_down_time, automatically change
service_down_time to be report_interval * 2.5 .

Closes bug #1261611

Change-Id: Icfa2a79d9df45a9674e8312f6ce67bc5a38275d2

[{'created': '2013-10-22 06:49:06.000000000', 'message': 'Fix inconsistent usages for network resources

If a normal user created a fixed_ip/floating_ip, a usage record with
column `in_use=1` will be created in the quota_usages table, and if an
admin user deleted the resource, a new record with column `in_use=-1`
will be created..This will cause the quota for the resources not
released.

Fixes bug 1220727

Change-Id: I705f2f9ef327a3198da6a47df772c3a1a28e1b4e
(cherry picked from commit f2dfdd4ab37965a6559f3c033cdf877e0fe172be)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix inconsistent usages for network resources

If a normal user created a fixed_ip/floating_ip, a usage record with
column `in_use=1` will be created in the quota_usages table, and if an
admin user deleted the resource, a new record with column `in_use=-1`
will be created..This will cause the quota for the resources not
released.

Fixes bug 1220727

Change-Id: I705f2f9ef327a3198da6a47df772c3a1a28e1b4e
(cherry picked from commit f2dfdd4ab37965a6559f3c033cdf877e0fe172be)

[{'created': '2013-12-16 11:19:05.000000000', 'message': 'Python 3: fix comparison between list and map

In HTTPretty, the query string is given as dictionary whose elements are maps,
which cannot becompared to a list in Python 3 without being converted to a list
first. Do that in assertQueryStringIs(), and use assertQueryStringIs where
appropriate.

Change-Id: I2827441815428148e3b0fb76de901c71c9a2f2f4
'}]
commit_message:
Python 3: fix comparison between list and map

In HTTPretty, the query string is given as dictionary whose elements are maps,
which cannot becompared to a list in Python 3 without being converted to a list
first. Do that in assertQueryStringIs(), and use assertQueryStringIs where
appropriate.

Change-Id: I2827441815428148e3b0fb76de901c71c9a2f2f4

I'd like to discuss this with the team.

With this change, we're now forcing the mount_point and the data_dir to be the same, and this might limit some configurations (where data_dir is not the mount point, but a directory contained within it for example). 

I like the fact that we're removing the two ways (conf + API) of specifying this, but I think that we should leave it in the conf, and not use the my.cnf data_dir value for it. 
 1. The data_dir and the mount point are logically different and could refer to different locations.
 2. I don't really like the fact that the guestagent now needs to know how to parse my.cnf and pull the value from there. With multiple datastores, this means that the guestagent code to parse multiple datastore config files, which I don't like."}, {'account_id': 8491, 'date': '2013-12-10 08:21:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 16:

commit_message:
Remove 'mount_point' from guestagent RPC API

Reason:
 - 'mount_point' is used inconsistently across guestagent code.
 - Sometimes its value is taken from parameters of RPC call
   and sometimes from CONF.
Changes:
 - Adding oslo mysql group. Now mount point retrieves
   via CONF.mysql.muont_point
 - This patch makes this value being taken from existing my.cnf.
 - 'mount_point' paramenter is removed from all trove-*.conf files.

Implements: blueprint remove-mount-point-from-parameters-for-instance-prepare
Closes-bug: 1248212

Change-Id: I2631f7b7cd0de9a13a20bd986b7f3fe8d363bf0e

This change introduces a template for logging.conf. I strongly disagree with the introduction a template for that file.

It removes a lot of flexility/agility to the end user, mainly the possibility to introduce his own file through private/internal manifests for various reasons. (one being that our module might never be flexible enough to his tastes without having to introduce a plethora of parameters)

Furthermore, Puppet is replacing a file provided by the distribution package by its own version. This is something our modules try very hard to not do. commit_message:
Add more granular logging support

cinder::logging provides the option to log cinder messages to
/var/log/cinder or to syslog. It also provides a minimal logging
threshold.
Added logging tests and moved to cinder_logging spec

Added new parameters to cinder class log_level and log_dir.

Change-Id: Iaa090083f66ae026c1ff5a4454a70390111734ac
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bogdando@mail.ru>

Sync oslo policy

Pull policy from oslo-incubator as of 339cdff. Previous version
of the policy module was updated more than year ago and therefore
it's pretty outdated.

Change-Id: I0c81130fc95c9f24b33bf5eb48e569919d00f95d

commit_message:
Bump webob requirements to include 1.3

Ubuntu 14.04 is shipping WebOb 1.3, which
passes test without a problem. Bump requirements
to include webob 1.3.

Change-Id: I2623b9397df417bc8b49cf77bc6d25427d2480f5
Signed-off-by: Chuck Short <chuck.short@canonical.com>

commit_message:
Fix fwaas and lbaas UI for NVP advanced service router

NVP advanced service plugin provides firewall and load balancer service on
an L3 router. The UI need to be enhanced to support extension attributes
for firewall, load balancer and advanced service router.

The following attributes are added to UI:
    Router: distributed and service_router
    Firewall: router_id
    Vip: router_id

Tests:
    - Deploy openstack using openvswitch as plugin, and use default
loadbalancer and firewall plugin. Verified Vip and Firewall can be created
via Horizon UI.
    - Deploy openstack using nvp advanced service router. Verified Vip and
Firewall can be created via Horizon UI on selected router.

Closes-Bug: #1231248
Change-Id: Id8155c3070af55381bf2dd89875852717002a553

Do you have an example where the new function is used to better understand the use case?

Also, I think the hot spec and template guide docs should be updated.'}, {'account_id': 7193, 'date': '2013-12-05 08:50:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

So I still don't get the use case, or at least not the desired user experience for template authors.

I am a bit concerned with adding such intrinsic functions to HOT and making it more and more a programming language as opposed to a declarative DSL for templates. If users really have to care about what happens to data structures when they are parsed and passed thru the engine, so care about wrapping things in functions, we are doing something wrong.

We argued about adding or not adding higher-level concepts like "components" to HOT and decided not to do it, and now we are bringing in low-level programming constructs. I don't think this will end up in good usability.'}, {'account_id': 4571, 'date': '2013-12-05 20:59:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I'll put together an email for the ML to explain my approach - it would be worth discussing anyway."}, {'account_id': 7256, 'date': '2013-12-06 21:46:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

Minor nit, but otherwise LGTM."}, {'account_id': 4571, 'date': '2013-12-09 02:55:45.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 4571, 'date': '2013-12-09 03:00:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Thomas, I started by implementing some cloud-init resources but they turned out to be doing just string manipulation, so intrinsic functions seemed much more appropriate as these very much in the same category of functions as str_replace.

Hopefully the added docs make the use case clear for this.

If you're worried about the proliferation of intrinsic functions in the HOT spec then maybe we need to decide whether functions belong in the spec at all."}, {'account_id': 4715, 'date': '2013-12-09 03:27:07.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I have no issue with the code changes, just a question:
Is it not possible to have a property of type yaml_string?
Then do the as_yaml_str in the type conversion in property.py
 (not sure on the feasibility - just asking)"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-12-09 03:28:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Works for me

commit_message:
Implement as_yaml_str hot intrinisic function

This would be useful to represent cloud-config using template
syntax structures rather than a string block.

For completeness, HOT probably needs an as_json_str function too.

partial blueprint cloud-init-resource

Change-Id: Id5f5cdf99a7f8fc38af0a66216ae6bced8cc7145

commit_message:
[PROOF OF CONCEPT] Integration testing

We are glad to introduce our concept of ironic's integration testing
implementation.

In short the actual scheme is very closer to the tripleo-ci, but might be
suitable only for ironic testing without all the unnecessary things.

All additional details would be disscussed on #openstack-ironic irc channel

Thanks for your time

Change-Id: I0d7759a0b599e7791f964ca18955cc4e503722ac

commit_message:
Do not pass bytes to json.loads()

In assertRequestBodyIs, we could end up passing bytes to json.loads(), thus
triggering a TypeError. We make sure to decode the value first if needed.

Change-Id: I720f895215ee2c230edc27c98e778536e0cbb2fa

This commit removes all the calls to TempestConfig() during import.
Doing this was causing errors when we ran pep8 and other jobs that
imports tempest files but did not have a config file when the job
was run.

This also moves the cli config group to tempest.config. Previously,
the cli tests used the traditional oslo.config global CONF object.
However, this could cause issues if the test order changed and/or if
there wasn't a strict dependency on the cli __init__.py file, but the
cli group was used in another file.

This commit removes all the calls to TempestConfig() during import.
Doing this was causing errors when we ran pep8 and other jobs that
imports tempest files but did not have a config file when the job
was run. For uses of config in skip decorators they are replaced
with a new method in the base test class skip_config() which is
used to raise a skip exception based on the config file.

the cli tests used the traditional oslo.config global CONF object.

commit_message:
Stop running TempestConfig() on import

This commit removes all the calls to TempestConfig() during import.
Doing this was causing errors when we ran pep8 and other jobs that
imports tempest files but did not have a config file when the job
was run. For uses of config in skip decorators they are replaced
with a new method in the base test class skip_config() which is
used to raise a skip exception based on the config file.

This also moves the cli config group to tempest.config. Previously,
the cli tests used the traditional oslo.config global CONF object.
However, this could cause issues if the test order changed and/or if
there wasn't a strict dependency on the cli __init__.py file, but the
cli group was used in another file.

Change-Id: I049c0d22d70e3b8142d00373ea41d89e7731290c

commit_message:
Fix for qemu-nbd hang (Take #2)

Additional check to see if the NBD device is still in the partition
list before we try to allocate it.

Change-Id: I4408783e03ec3653fe76683d744186610c2b32ee
Closes-Bug: #973413
Partial-Bug: #1254890

commit_message:
Attach volume eventhough the instance is shutoff

It should be possible to attach a volume to a shutoff instance.
Nova CLI (nova volume-attach) allows this and Horizon should be
on par.

Change-Id: Ie7c351e5b23f218d6d10c80b9aebbf233c62b7be
Closes-Bug: 1251255

commit_message:
Fix incorrect exception on os-migrateLive

If the server state is conflict to live-migrate, it raises
400(HTTPBadRequest)exception.We should raise HTTPConflict instead of
HTTPBadRequest.

Change-Id: I40ccb0f268716da20ae4b3de9d295a41a2dba18d
Closes-Bug: #1255001

commit_message:
Fix "device" as the optional para on volume-attach

Attach a volume to a server without device name, the client returned the
error msg: "error: too few arguments". But for server, we can attach a
volume to a server without the device name.

Change-Id: Ia2743c6e3956cae6591ecd414baf89b0dbcf532b
Closes-Bug: #1257137

commit_message:
Remove start index 0 in range()

Remove the useless arg ("start index" = 0) in files, since its default
value is 0, to make code cleaner.

Fixes bug #1261580

Change-Id: Ieeace91e8cbd540ddccd8288002331a6e5a70c58

This is a nasty bug, so using the metadata seems like a clever way to squash the it quickly. 

    
    But this seems like a standard state machine problem, where expected the state transition fails and you have to decide what error state to leave the device in. In that case this might be best addressed by implementing the delete operation in task flow, and making sure that the solution is general. But this bug is probably too urgent to wait for that.
    

    I also think that to squash this bug quickly it might be valid to always move to the state to error if the delete fails. commit_message:
Revert to previous status if volume busy on delete

Currently when deleting a volume and it is busy, the manager will set
the status to 'available', even if the volume was in an error state. The
solution here is to save the previous state in the volume's
admin_metadata, and set to that.

Change-Id: Ic1eaf95424b874ab9a89058dd32c37dda17efd5b
Closes-Bug: #1236165

commit_message:
ValueError should use '%' instead of ','

ValueError do not support using ',' to connect log and variables,
we should use '%' instead.

Change-Id: I04c2002a970465d8250e5550f6bf992b48845a0d
Closes-Bug: #1261621

commit_message:
Move workspace setup to functions.sh

And add a test script that exercises the logic of the git repo
checkout functions.  Current test errors are annotated and commented
out.

commit_message:
Support MTU configuration of L3 managed interfaces

network_device_mtu configure the MTU for L3 managed network interfaces.
By default no specific network_device_mtu configuration is set. The
interface defaults will be used as they got created.

This options allows configuration of Jumbo Frame usage.

Change-Id: Ic5de813532b744fcd5ee289f10fb28e587b3699f

commit_message:

commit_message:
Fix for qemu-nbd hang

Do a lazy un-mount (-l during umount) and disable the
host cache when creating the qemu-nbd connection. This
combination seems to avoid the hangs we see in the
tempest runs. The symptom seen in the logs was if
there was a problem during a previous unmount (say /dev/nbd6)
then a subsequent mount with the same device will hang.

Closes-Bug: #973413
Partial-Bug: #1254890

Change-Id: I0f9d034d18b71ef27593a0030f8edc43573f61e5

commit_message:
default_network changes for overcloud

These are the changes I needed to make to get the default_network
change working in my tripleo overcloud.  With this, all of the
tests that were previously failing due to the multiple available
networks problem are working again.

The changes themselves are:

Tweaked the XML server create so it only adds the fixed_ip
attribute if there is a fixed ip.

default_network was overriding the networks passed in some tests,
so I changed it to check if the kwarg exists before setting it.

Change-Id: Ib8d78360612ef554ca80ce4e779672b03356b6e0

[{'created': '2013-12-23 22:49:08.000000000', 'message': "Fix OS_TEST_PATH in .testr.conf

As of commit 87f772c0bd59790aa43de59938d9c138963f9f4e the default
value for OS_TEST_PATH as set in .testr.conf is no longer valid.

In addition, because shell variables are evaluated in a
somewhat unintuitive order in situations like this, the default
wasn't being used properly anyway.  See link below for an
explanation why:

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/10938483/bash-specifying-environment-variables-for-echo-on-command-line

This commit fixes both problems.

commit_message:
Fix OS_TEST_PATH in .testr.conf

As of commit 87f772c0bd59790aa43de59938d9c138963f9f4e the default
value for OS_TEST_PATH as set in .testr.conf is no longer valid.

In addition, because shell variables are evaluated in a
somewhat unintuitive order in situations like this, the default
wasn't being used properly anyway.  See link below for an
explanation why:

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/10938483/bash-specifying-environment-variables-for-echo-on-command-line

This commit fixes both problems.

Change-Id: I8eec146a21eab656cb48b9e23a92a9da52246269

Add `port` attribute to Server object

Ssh server can run not only on tcp port 22. Also removed unused
attribute `uuid`.

bug 1261754

Change-Id: I1832ac5549960c2d1661510dbb728e0372a92230

2.21.0.

commit_message:
Blacklist boto 2.21.1

Grenade is having issues with euca and bundle tests in grenade. Both use
boto, and the euca2ools commands work again when switching back to boto
2.21.0.

Change-Id: Ie395f5624849b67b632851fdb740e8ed037f06c9
Related-Bug: #1263824
(cherry picked from commit cc8a8cb2580fd9cc2b0229f26ea8c73bdeffd99d)

Previous default for eswitch/daemon_endpoint would set a TCP port (5001)
which is in the range of the well known ports.
Change to unreserved port (60001) will avoid that conflict.

Change-Id: I711c4659f497e44a6041ec9958835c1f2f4174a7
Closes-Bug: #1245885
(cherry picked from commit cd542a7f1f2ea21d3694e70b8e6a6db0efbd3a01)
'}]
commit_message:
Change default eswitchd port to avoid conflict

Previous default for eswitch/daemon_endpoint would set a TCP port (5001)
which is in the range of the well known ports.
Change to unreserved port (60001) will avoid that conflict.

Change-Id: I711c4659f497e44a6041ec9958835c1f2f4174a7
Closes-Bug: #1245885
(cherry picked from commit cd542a7f1f2ea21d3694e70b8e6a6db0efbd3a01)

commit_message:
Rename dynamic_ui package and normalize it.

* Move muranodashboard.environments.services package to
  muranodashboard.dynamic_ui.
* Move all code from dynamic_ui/__init__.py to dynamic_ui/services.py
  thus having normal empty __init__.py for dynamic_ui package (as in
  other packages).

Change-Id: I395ee621578cb417314fe4960d74108deb848023

commit_message:
Fix ssh port in devstack engine

When changing user from root to DEVSTACK_USER, ssh port has
been dropped.

Closes-Bug: #1261751

Change-Id: I1c5face4f00624f59f06a6c39c050350d5489db3

commit_message:
Do not check the status of a job execution if Oozie id is None

New job executions may not have an Oozie id assigned right away.
Skip the periodic status update for such jobs until the Oozie id
is no longer None.

Closes-Bug: #1263785
Change-Id: I26da336ff52962c1644ceba641428d2311950377

commit_message:
Don't provide default values to properties.get()

The properties of a resource are known, so we don't need to provide
default values to properties.get().

Change-Id: I2c28d9fe41db589a885c458dba35780aabed87c0

commit_message:
Remove useless validate methods

Remove the validate methods of s3 and swift resources, as they don't
provide any value and hide validation of properties.

Change-Id: I5b9f7aef828d5e4d7cdebfd2bd550feaae545c90
Closes-Bug: #1260643

commit_message:
Moved tests for general utils out of vanilla package

test_utils are used by tests for general code. They should not be in 'vanilla' package.
The next logical step is to split "tests for utils" and "utils for tests".
But at least tests better reflect to objects structure now.

Change-Id: I0adb77d8c55893ae74eb4a73dd7fb69c82ebe9bb

commit_message:
Keystone ADMIN_TOKEN autogenerated

If the user doesn't enter one using Debconf, then the Debian
package will automatically generate a ADMIN_TOKEN. This
needed to be properly documented, which is what this patch
does.

Change-Id: Ide85feb9c7bae233563a653c2be0a85609e33697

commit_message:
Added new OSTF tests for Murano 0.4

Added OSTF tests for new Murano services:
 Demo Service (simple service based on CentOS image)
 Apache Service (Linux-based service)
 Telnet Service (Linux-based service)

Also fixed logic for image search to support different
Murano images types.

Fixed issue with changed windows images tag.

Change-Id: Ief56732f450f6ed14f47b70e82e04957a7770c17
Implements: blueprint new-ostf-tests-for-murano04

commit_message:
Add timeout for ceph recovery

When user destroy osd-node from cluster,
ceph requires ~5 min for recovering.

Improvement for ceph_ha test.

Change-Id: I6e12223ca6602d82182323c8b264c787c43e0f04

commit_message:
Fixed AMQP configuration steps for Block Storage

I fixed the AMQP configuration steps in cinder.conf for Block Storage
on both controller and service nodes. I also unified structure and
phrasing with other portions of the guide and mentioned replacing
'RABBIT_PASS'. This patch affects all distributions.

I also found and fixed a minor issue causing several database
configuration instructions for other distributions to leak into those
for Debian which uses Debconf.

Change-Id: Ifd6f185b422195a00aad6efa83418d34b93eac85
backport: havana
Closes-Bug: #1244781

Improve behaviour of the Galera rebuild.

Decreasing timeout down to moment of quorum creation for corosync.

Join to healthy cluster takes about 20 seconds.

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-12-24 05:09:20.000000000', 'message': 'Fix copying of select-mirror outputs.

The Jenkins user was attempting to write to ~stack and failing because
it does not have permission to do so. Use more sudo to get around that.
Additionally move the fix for /etc/hosts into setup_host instead of
setup_workspace. This will make the use of sudo quieter as it will be
able to resolve $HOSTNAME earlier.

Change-Id: I8e6bd821ceac9d0614c068dc7ce7a6657329d84c
'}]
commit_message:
Fix copying of select-mirror outputs.

The Jenkins user was attempting to write to ~stack and failing because
it does not have permission to do so. Use more sudo to get around that.
Additionally move the fix for /etc/hosts into setup_host instead of
setup_workspace. This will make the use of sudo quieter as it will be
able to resolve $HOSTNAME earlier.

Change-Id: I8e6bd821ceac9d0614c068dc7ce7a6657329d84c

commit_message:
Increase memory size for slaves

New components (like heat) are actively using swap,
we should increase mem.size for improvement of deployment.

There is a race on inserting row into table when reserve_provider_segment()
Fix it by utilizing primary key constraint instead of table locking.

commit_message:
ml2/type driver: race on reserve_provider_segment

There is a race on inserting row into table when reserve_provider_segment()
Fix it by utilizing primary key constraint instead of table locking.

Change-Id: Id162b4fa2fc5d82efa089c901e3525ffc97e6999
Closes-Bug: #1260598
Signed-off-by: Isaku Yamahata <isaku.yamahata@intel.com>

[{'created': '2013-10-26 00:39:04.000000000', 'message': 'VMware: Fix VSAN datastores cannot be used

THIS IS WIP
(probably will have to break it up into a few smaller patches)

Summary of changes:
- Added selection of datastores of "vsan" type
- Added image import via HttpNfc. HttpNfc is the only viable
  means to import a disk to a vSAN datastore in the absence of any other
  temporary datastore storage.
- Added support for new vmdk format 'streamOptimized'
  It is a compact, compressed streamable sparse format that is well-suited as a
  vmdk glance image format.  Just as important, this is the only format that
  HttpNfc supports, so it is the required format for deploying to VSAN
- Basic handling image caching as an imported VM instead of a disk
- Handle instance delete of vsan-based VM differently (through the more
  straightforward Delete_Task)

TODOs:
- Fix/add unit tests.
- Implement nova snapshot->glance upload of VSAN VM root disk via httpnfc

Known issue:
- instance delete will delete attached volumes as well. This is being
  addressed in another fix I believe via detaching before delete
- need to add unit tests
- streamOptimized image caches different on the datastore due to the
  different import mechanism, so there will be coordination with the
  upcoming image cache management work.

Change-Id: I0aca0525c91e4001b4bf14216e7be1fbf026fb13

commit_message:
VMware: Fix VSAN datastores cannot be used

THIS IS WIP
(probably will have to break it up into a few smaller patches)

Summary of changes:
- Added selection of datastores of "vsan" type.
- Added image import via HttpNfc. HttpNfc is the only viable means to import a
  disk to a vSAN datastore in the absence of any other temporary datastore
  storage.
- Implemented nova snapshot->glance upload of vSAN VM root disk via HttpNfc
- Added support for new vmdk format 'streamOptimized'.
  It is a compact, compressed streamable sparse format that is well-suited as a
  vmdk glance image format.  Just as important, this is the only format that
  HttpNfc supports, so it is the required format for deploying to vSAN
- Handling of image caching as an imported VM instead of a disk
- Handle instance delete of vsan-based VM differently (through the more
  straightforward Delete_Task)

TODOs:
- Add unit tests.

Known issue:
- Instance delete will delete attached volumes as well. This is being
  addressed in another fix.
- StreamOptimized image caches differently on the datastore due to the
  different import mechanism, so there will be additional coordination with the
  upcoming image cache management work.

Closes-Bug: #1244752
Change-Id: I0aca0525c91e4001b4bf14216e7be1fbf026fb13

commit_message:
xen: add namespace for diagnostics (v3 API only)

There is no formal definition for the VM diagnostics. For the
V2 API the diagnostics will be returned as they are today. For the V3
api the diagnostics will be prefixed with the driver namespace.

That is the diagnostics will be returned as follows:
{'xen': {'key1': 'value1',
         'key2': 'value2',
         ...}}

This will support backward compatibility with the existing API's.

Part of the blueprint diagnostics-namespace

DocImpact

Change-Id: I37fbf9ac9fa1afe6086121692a83b9178d2cb7db

commit_message:
Added ability to specify kernel command line for an instance

The KernelCommandLine extension provides ability to specify the kernel
command line as a property of a glance image.  This value is then
used as the kernel command line for nova instances started using this
glance image.  This extension also allows the command line to be
specified through the nova REST api for creating instances.

Change-Id: I4564f32d2d279d54f5da82da33731956d2f76184

The main thrust of the argument to remove uuidutils.generate_uuid() from oslo, is that it adds no appreciable value over calling str(uuid.uuid4()) directly. This is just stupid. As described before there are only two scenarios which make any kind of sense here

 1. oslo removes the generate_uuid method and all projects call uuid.uuid4() directly
 2. oslo keeps its generate_uuid method and all projects use that

This change is proposing the worst possible option

 3. olso removes its generate_uuid() method an all projects re-create their own generate_uuid() method.

If oslo is not prepared to do option 2, then we should follow option 1."}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2013-12-15 00:06:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

need to remove its use in nova

Change-Id: I4506696d50669f16810d4c7c2cd9d21b78bf1f4d
Closes-Bug: #1253497
'}, {'created': '2013-11-21 04:17:57.000000000', 'message': 'Replace uuidutils.generate_uuid() with uuid.uuid4() in nova

uuidutils.generate_uuid() is going to be removed from oslo, so we
need to remove its use in nova.

http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2013-November/
018980.html

This patch was use uuid.uuid4() to replace uuidutils.generate_uuid(),
also I was using "import uuid as stdlib_uuid" to import uuid, the
reason is that in nova code, there are many variables named as uuid
and directly import uuid will be shadowed by the variables named as
uuid.

Change-Id: I4506696d50669f16810d4c7c2cd9d21b78bf1f4d

commit_message:
Remove oslo uuidutils.generate_uuid call from nova

uuidutils.generate_uuid is going to be removed from oslo, so we
need to remove the call from nova code.

http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2013-November/
018980.html

This patch create new method in our nova utils to wrap the
uuid.uuid4() methods.

Change-Id: I4506696d50669f16810d4c7c2cd9d21b78bf1f4d
Partial-Bug: #1253497

commit_message:
Benchmark scenarios for Rally: Nova server metadata

The patch provides Rally with the basic Nova benchmark scenario for server
metadata: the scenario implements setting and deleting a set of fake metadata
records for a prepared server.

Blueprint benchmark-scenarios

Change-Id: I9f61d5f11d176ba654c8a0280ad8bf547f7d9336

subject: Introduce Generic Parsing/Filtering Framework
messages:
[{'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2013-11-22 16:06:46.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

this is going to take me a little longer for a full review, I like a lot of what I see in here, but I want to make sure I understand it fully before merge (on an airplane with 3hrs sleep, so now isn't ideal time for that). There is one specific quick change on tests which would be nice.

I'm also curious why this changes the number of lines at a level in the test? Is this no longer doing spill over levels (i.e. if a follow on line doesn't have a severity, it should go with the last line's severity).

Thanks for this so far, will take another look in depth either this weekend or monday."}, {'account_id': 7677, 'date': '2013-11-22 17:56:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Yes, that was the reason for the change.  It means, among other things, that blank lines are not counted as having a severity (they are set as "none").  I could attempt to tweak the architecture to attempt to include the last line's severity (assuming the line is not blank).  Would that be better?'}, {'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2013-11-25 14:25:48.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

so adding the intersticial lines as the last severity is actually kind of important as there are multi line dumps of things like XML that don't get caught otherwise.

I think that the blank line problem becomes a separate issue we go after in the projects themselves and fix it there. As there is no reason that a project should log a blank line (IIRC keystone was the major culprit).

So if you could respin these and keep the old behavior of keeping the last line severity for lines that don't have one, that would be great."}, {'account_id': 7677, 'date': '2013-11-26 20:24:02.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-11-26 20:25:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Works for me

Build succeeded.

- gate-os-loganalyze-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/84/57784/2/check/gate-os-loganalyze-pep8/62afe8d : SUCCESS in 49s
- gate-os-loganalyze-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/84/57784/2/check/gate-os-loganalyze-python27/c57ebcd : SUCCESS in 1m 38s
'}, {'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2013-11-26 22:36:54.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(2 inline comments)

ok, my brain is wrapping around the matcher pipes. There are a couple of things.

Instead of passing around tuples and dicts and merging them, can you create a data structure for the results that has methods on it to do the right thing. I'm less keen on res[0] needing to be in the code and to realize why you only want the first part of that. I think a datastructure wrapper for the results as being processed would be helpful.

Secondly, as inline comments said, I don't want to drop lines by default. I think if we are realizing there is something in the logs which is completely noise, like blank lines or raw amqp, we should try to fix that in the core project. [{'created': '2013-11-21 21:48:01.000000000', 'message': "Introduce Generic Parsing/Filtering Framework

This commit introduces a new, generic framework for writing
log prettifiers.  LogMatchers parse or filter log line parts,
and are chained together to form full matchers.  The output of
these chains (a dict or nested dicts) is passed into an outputter,
which applies styles to the output.  Outputters delegate the actual
details of how a style is applied to stylers.  This way, a single
set of matchers and a single outputter can be used regardless of
the output medium.  Only the styler has to be differed.

The WSGI filter has been updated to use the new framework, and common
code between the passthrough filter and the html filter has been
pulled out into its own method which constructs the appropriate filter
chains.

The framework includes several filters which take arguments, and thus
the following query string parameters have been introduced:

- filter_sev: used to explicitly override the automatic severity
              detection.  When not specified, the filter checks
              whether a level has been specified in the query
              string (which acts like 'filter_sev=True').  If
              no level is present, it falls back on the
              filename-based detection.

- log_type: used to explicitly override the log file type detection.
            if not specified, the filename-based detection will be used.
            May be 'console', 'keystone', 'devstack', or 'oslo'

- no_match (default: false): explicitly disables matching/filtering functionality
                             for the passthrough filter, in case you
                             just want the log file directly for some
                             reason

- skip_raw (default: true): skip lines the 'raw' AMQP message lines,
                            when appropriate

- skip_source (multiple): skip lines whose 'source' matches the given
                          regular expression (note that spaces are
                          treated as '+' in the regexp, so use '\s'
                          for a space instead).

This is commit 2/4

Change-Id: Iffb6b7366c64cdef6f7657ecab64caaede6af882

commit_message:
Introduce Generic Parsing/Filtering Framework

This commit introduces a new, generic framework for writing
log prettifiers.  LogMatchers parse or filter log line parts,
and are chained together to form full matchers.  The output of
these chains (a dict or nested dicts) is passed into an outputter,
which applies styles to the output.  Outputters delegate the actual
details of how a style is applied to stylers.  This way, a single
set of matchers and a single outputter can be used regardless of
the output medium.  Only the styler has to be differed.

The WSGI filter has been updated to use the new framework, and common
code between the passthrough filter and the html filter has been
pulled out into its own method which constructs the appropriate filter
chains.

The framework includes several filters which take arguments, and thus
the following query string parameters have been introduced:

- filter_sev: used to explicitly override the automatic severity
              detection.  When not specified, the filter checks
              whether a level has been specified in the query
              string (which acts like 'filter_sev=True').  If
              no level is present, it falls back on the
              filename-based detection.

- log_type: used to explicitly override the log file type detection.
            if not specified, the filename-based detection will be used.
            May be 'console', 'keystone', 'devstack', or 'oslo'

- no_match (default: false): explicitly disables matching/filtering functionality
                             for the passthrough filter, in case you
                             just want the log file directly for some
                             reason

- skip_raw (default: true): skip lines the 'raw' AMQP message lines,
                            when appropriate

- skip_source (multiple): skip lines whose 'source' matches the given
                          regular expression (note that spaces are
                          treated as '+' in the regexp, so use '\s'
                          for a space instead).

This is commit 2/4

Change-Id: Iffb6b7366c64cdef6f7657ecab64caaede6af882

The cache type used for volume storage is configurable since long,
but we did not have an option for the ephemeral storage.

The built in option does not have the pest performance with every
storage setup, however it provides the best chances to survive a power
outage.
Let the users the pick cache type which fits to their requirements.

The "none" cache type is not usable in several other situations,
like when the storage has stricter alignment requirements,
 for example xfs file-system created with 4k sector size, requires all
O_DIRECT I/O request is aligned to 4k.

Change-Id: I3b03862a1037b931948c8c464cbebc67fe3538f2
